\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\itap0{\*\bkmkstart _Toc35011439}{\*\bkmkend _Toc31381209}{\f0\fs34\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch II. The External Look and That Which \line Is Human}{\*\bkmkend _Toc31381383}{\*\bkmkend _Toc35011439}{\f0\fs34\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 1.\tab Nothing substantial is being said when we are told that \uc1\u8220\'93Human beings are constituted by their environment.\uc1\u8221\'94 Nor when it is said that \uc1\u8220\'93thanks to the environment (environment being understood by some as natural, by others as social, and by still others as both natural and social) the human being is constituted.\uc1\u8221\'94 This idea appears all the more inconsistent when we focus on the relationship implied by the word \uc1\u8220\'93constituted\uc1\u8221\'94\uc1\u8212\'97assuming, of course, that we already understand the terms \uc1\u8220\'93human being\uc1\u8221\'94 and \uc1\u8220\'93environment.\uc1\u8221\'94 Presumably, \uc1\u8220\'93environment\uc1\u8221\'94 is that which surrounds the human being, or better, that in which the human being is immersed, and the \uc1\u8220\'93human being\uc1\u8221\'94 is that which is within or immersed in that \uc1\u8220\'93environment.\uc1\u8221\'94 }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi244\li274\ri274\s44\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx1595\tx2315\tx3755\tx4475\tx5915\tx6635\tx8075\tx8358{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch We find ourselves, then, as at the beginning, in a circle of vacuities. Though the two terms being related point to separate entities, we can observe an intention to unite them in a deceptive relationship through the use of the word \uc1\u8220\'93constitute}{\s44\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8221\'94\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}a word that has implications of genesis, that is to say, of}{\s44\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0} }{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}explaining something by means of its origins.}{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 2.\tab This assertion would be of no particular interest were it not for the fact that it is presented as a paradigm of similar assertions that for millennia have offered an image of the human being as seen from the }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}outside}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}. That is, looking at the human being from the standpoint of things and not from the standpoint of the look that looks at things. To say \uc1\u8220\'93the human being is a social animal\uc1\u8221\'94 or \uc1\u8220\'93man is made in the image of God\uc1\u8221\'94 is to make society or God into the entity that looks at the human being, while in reality it is only from the }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}human look}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} that society and God are conceived, and accepted or denied. }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 3.\tab And so, in a world where an inhuman look has long been established, there have also been established behaviors and institutions that annihilate our humanity. So it was that one of the questions that arose in the observation of nature concerned the \uc1\u8220\'93nature\uc1\u8221\'94 of the human being, and the responses that were given were like those that might be given about any natural object. }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}4.\tab Even those currents of thought that have presented the human being as subject to continuing transformation have considered }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}what is human}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} from within one of the several perspectives of historical naturalism\uc1\u8212\'97that is, from an external look. }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 5.\tab The underlying idea of \uc1\u8220\'93human nature\uc1\u8221\'94 corresponds to an external look directed at that which is human. But human beings are historical beings whose mode of social action transforms their own nature. Knowing this subordinates the concept of \uc1\u8220\'93human nature\uc1\u8221\'94 to existence and its tasks\uc1\u8212\'97making it subject to the transformations and revelations directed by this existence. Thus, the body, as the prosthesis of intention, extends its potentialities through humanizing the world\uc1\u8212\'97a world that can no longer be seen as simple externality but instead as a }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}landscape,}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} natural or human, that is subject to present or possible transformations. And it is through this activity that the human being also transforms itself. }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
{\listtext\pard\fi-311\li326\ri274 5.	}\pard\plain{\ltrpar\ql\fi-311\li326\ri274\s53{\*\abilist\abilistid1131\abilistparentid0\abilistlevel1\abistartat5{\abifieldfont }{\abilistdecimal .}{\abilistdelim %L.}{\abiliststyle Numbered List}}{\*\pn\pnql\pnstart5\pnlvlbody\pndec{\pntxtb }{\pntxta .}}\fn-311\li326\ls2\ilvl0\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx326\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358}
