\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 1.\tab The body, as a natural object, is subject to natural modifications, and thanks to human intention is, of course, susceptible to transformation\uc1\u8212\'97not only in its most external expressions but also in its innermost functioning. One\uc1\u8217\'92s own body takes on its greatest significance when viewed in this way\uc1\u8212\'97as the }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}prosthesis of intention.}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} However, a social process intervenes between the immediate (unmediated) governance of one\uc1\u8217\'92s own body and the adaptation of the body to the needs and purposes of others. This process does not depend on the isolated individual but entails others as well.}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 2.\tab Ownership of my psychophysical structure is given by my intentionality, while external objects present themselves to me as only indirectly subject to my control (through the action of my body) and outside of my immediate ownership. There is a particular type of object, however, that I intuit as the property of a foreign intention, and that is the body of the other. That }{\s53\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}otherness }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}puts me in the position of being \uc1\u8220\'93seen from outside,\uc1\u8221\'94 seen from someone else\uc1\u8217\'92s intention. My vision of the other is, therefore, an interpretation\uc1\u8212\'97a landscape extending to every object that carries the mark of human intention, whether produced or used today or in the past.}{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi244\li274\ri274\s44\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx1595\tx2315\tx3755\tx4475\tx5915\tx6635\tx8075\tx8358{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch In that human landscape I can obliterate the intention of others by considering them prostheses of my own body, in which case I must \uc1\u8220\'93empty\uc1\u8221\'94 them of their subjectivity, at least in those areas of thought, feeling, or action that I wish to control directly. But this objectification of others necessarily dehumanizes me as well, and so I justify this situation by claiming that it is the consequence of \uc1\u8220\'93Passion,\uc1\u8221\'94 \uc1\u8220\'93God,\uc1\u8221\'94 \uc1\u8220\'93A Cause,\uc1\u8221\'94 \uc1\u8220\'93Natural Inequity,\uc1\u8221\'94 \uc1\u8220\'93Fate,\uc1\u8221\'94 \uc1\u8220\'93Society,\uc1\u8221\'94 and so forth. }{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
