\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 1.\tab When faced with an unfamiliar landscape, I appeal to my memory and notice as \uc1\u8220\'93new\uc1\u8221\'94 that which I \uc1\u8220\'93recognize\uc1\u8221\'94 as absent in myself. The same thing occurs in a human landscape, where today\uc1\u8217\'92s language, clothing, and customs contrast sharply with that landscape in which my memories were formed. In a society where change is slow, however, my previous landscape tends to overwhelm these novel aspects, and I dismiss them as \uc1\u8220\'93irrelevant.\uc1\u8221\'94 }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab  2.\tab If I live in a society in which change occurs very swiftly, I tend not to recognize the value of change or to consider it \uc1\u8220\'93superficial,\uc1\u8221\'94 without realizing that the inner loss I experience is the loss of that social landscape in which my memory was formed. }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 3.\tab Thanks to all of this I understand that when a generation comes to power, it tends to give external expression to the myths and theories, the desires, appetites, and values of its formative landscapes\uc1\u8212\'97landscapes that no longer exist yet still live and act in the social memory of the landscape in which this group was formed. It also happens that the landscape that children assimilate as the human landscape is seen by their parents as \uc1\u8220\'93irrelevant\uc1\u8221\'94 or a \uc1\u8220\'93diversion.\uc1\u8221\'94 }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi244\li274\ri274\s44\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx1595\tx2315\tx3755\tx4475\tx5915\tx6635\tx8075\tx8358{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch However fiercely the generations may struggle between themselves, when a new generation comes to power it immediately becomes obstructionist, attempting to impose its own landscape of formation on a human landscape that has already changed\uc1\u8212\'97and which that generation itself may even have helped to change. Thus, in those transformations instituted by the group that is in power there are, dragged along from its formative years, the obstructions against which the newer group that is forming will clash. }{\s44\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi274\ri274\s105\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tx0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800{\s105\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch When I have spoken of the \uc1\u8220\'93power\uc1\u8221\'94 that a generation acquires, I trust that I have been correctly understood as referring to power in all its forms: political, social, cultural, and so forth. }{\s105\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
