\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 1.\tab \uc1\u8220\'93Your rights end where the rights of others begin.\uc1\u8221\'94 Therefore: \uc1\u8220\'93The rights of others end where your rights begin.\uc1\u8221\'94 However, since it is generally the first and not the second phrase that is emphasized, we are led to suspect that those who maintain this position see themselves as \uc1\u8220\'93the others\uc1\u8221\'94\uc1\u8212\'97that is, as the representatives of all other people, as the representatives of an established system that needs no justification. }{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
