\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-547\li273\ri274\s53\sl280\slmult0\itap0\tqdec\tx80\tx260\tx875\tx1595\tx2315\tx3035\tx3755\tx4475\tx5195\tx5915\tx6635\tx7355\tx8075\tx8358{\s53\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab 1.\tab That which is said about things and events is not the things and the events themselves, but rather \uc1\u8220\'93figures\uc1\u8221\'94 that have a certain structure in common with them. Thanks to that common structure, it is possible to talk about things and events. That structure, however, cannot in turn be talked about in the same way that things are talked about because it is the structure of that which is being said as well as of things and events. Thus, language can point to, but not speak of, that which \uc1\u8220\'93includes\uc1\u8221\'94 everything (even language itself). Such is the case of \uc1\u8220\'93God.\uc1\u8221\'94 }
