\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\li-431\ri-431\sb119\sa60\s47\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s47\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The Internal Landscape}{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} is divided into eighteen chapters, which are subdivided into numbered passages. The principal themes can be grouped as follows:}{\s47\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab Chapters I and II are introductory and direct questions to the reader about his or her happiness, suffering, and interests in life.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab Chapters III through VI examine the different types of landscapes\uc1\u8212\'97external, human, and internal\uc1\u8212\'97and their interaction.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab Chapter VII touches on the themes of pain, suffering, and meaning in life. These points, and others related to valid action in the world, are further developed through Chapter XIII.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab In Chapters XIV through XVIII the central themes are the motives and direction of human actions, along with proposals for change in the meaning of life. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\li-431\ri-431\sb119\sa60\s47\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The topics appear in the following order:}{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab I.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Question}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Queries the reader about happiness and suffering. Proposes a direction toward overcoming suffering.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab II.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Reality}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Discusses the nature of the \uc1\u8220\'93real,\uc1\u8221\'94 relating what one perceives to the conformation of the human being.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab III.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The External Landscape\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Points out that every external landscape varies according to what is happening within the one who is perceiving it.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab IV.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Human Landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Shows how the human landscape involves the interior of the person. Denies the right of factions or special interests to demand that others must adopt their answers to the problems that individuals and societies currently face. Affirms the need to define action toward the human world.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab V.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Internal Landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Explains that at the base of all human activity lie beliefs. Emphasizes, however, that the internal landscape is not only a field of beliefs but of memories, perceptions, and images as well. Observes that the relation }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}internal-external landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} is a structure in which both terms are correlates and can alternately be taken as acts or objects. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VI.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Center and Reflection\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Indicates the possibility of placing oneself in the center of the internal landscape, from which any direction chosen is a reflection of this center. Shows that the path to learning lies through action and not solely through contemplation.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Pain, Suffering, and Meaning in Life}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Distinguishes between physical pain and mental suffering. Introduces the phrase \uc1\u8220\'93Humanize the Earth\uc1\u8221\'94 as the key to meaning in life, emphasizing the primacy of the future over the present or the past.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VIII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Rider and His Shadow\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Breaks the monotony of previous chapters with a shift in style. Nevertheless, again considers the problems of the different times in human life (past, present, and future), seeking in them the root of memory, perception, and imagination. These three pathways are later considered \uc1\u8220\'93the three pathways of suffering\uc1\u8221\'94 to the extent that contradiction inverts the times of consciousness.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab IX.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Contradiction and Unity\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Continues to explore the interplay of the various times in human life. Emphasizes the differences between everyday problems or difficulties on the one hand, and contradiction on the other, presenting the defining characteristics of contradiction. Proposes changes in the organization of the internal landscape.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab X.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Valid Action\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Explains that not only contradiction but all inversion in the growing current of life generates suffering. Emphasizes the importance of }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}valid actions}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} as unifying acts that are capable of overcoming contradiction. Presents an implicit critique of the foundations of morality when not developed based on the need to give unity to the human being, to provide references for surpassing contradiction and suffering.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XI.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Projection of the Internal Landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Emphasizes that both contradictory and unifying acts commit the future of those who produce them, as well as the future of all who are in contact with them. In this sense, individual contradiction \uc1\u8220\'93contaminates\uc1\u8221\'94 others, while individual unity also affects others.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Compensation, Reflection, and the Future}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97The background of this chapter is the age-old debate between determinism and freedom. Concisely reviews the mechanics of human actions as the interplay of compensatory actions as well as the reflection of the external landscape, without overlooking accidents as another phenomenon capable of undoing all human projects. Finally, emphasizes the search for the growth of life without limit as a leap over determining conditions.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XIII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Provisional Meanings\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Outlines the dialectic between \uc1\u8220\'93provisional meanings\uc1\u8221\'94 and \uc1\u8220\'93meaning in life.\uc1\u8221\'94 Places affirmation of life as the highest value, suggesting that it is the rebellion against death that drives all progress. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XIV.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Faith}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Notes the feeling of suspicion experienced upon hearing the word \uc1\u8220\'93faith.\uc1\u8221\'94 Distinguishes between naive faith, fanatical faith, and faith applied in the service of life. Gives faith maximum importance as the energy that mobilizes all enthusiasm in life.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XV.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}To Give and To Receive}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Establishes that the act of giving opens the future, and that all valid actions go in this direction. Receiving, in contrast, is centripetal, and dies in the individual. It is through giving that one can change the direction of a contradictory life.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XVI.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Models}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Explains \uc1\u8220\'93models\uc1\u8221\'94 as the internal images that motivate human activities toward the external world, while noting that such images are modified with changes in the internal landscape.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XVII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Internal Guide}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Refers to the existence of models in the internal landscape that are examples of how to act. Such models can be called \uc1\u8220\'93internal guides.\uc1\u8221\'94 }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XVIII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Change\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Studies the possibility of voluntary change in human conduct. }{\*\bkmkstart _Toc31381398}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc31381854}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc35011454}{\*\bkmkend _Toc31381398}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\li1440\ri1440\sb220\sa220\s48\sl310\slmult0\itap0{\s48\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The Human Landscape}{\*\bkmkend _Toc31381854}{\*\bkmkend _Toc35011454}{\s48\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0} }{\s48\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\li-431\ri-431\sb119\sa60\s47\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s47\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The Human Landscape}{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} is divided into thirteen chapters, which are subdivided into numbered passages. The principal themes can be grouped as follows:}{\s47\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab The first five chapters are dedicated to clarifying the meaning of the human landscape and the }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}look}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} that is related to that landscape.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab The following seven chapters address central questions that arise in the human landscape.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab \uc1\u8226\'95\tab Chapter thirteen concludes the themes developed, inviting the reader to continue the study of important issues that have been treated only in passing in this work. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\li-431\ri-431\sb119\sa60\s47\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The topics appear in the following order: }{\s47\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab I.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Looks and Landscapes\uc1\u8212\'97}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Establishes the difference between internal, external, and human landscapes. Introduces distinctions between }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}looks}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} of different types}{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab II.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The External Look and That Which Is Human}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Reviews what has been said about the human being from an \uc1\u8220\'93external look.\uc1\u8221\'94}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab III.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Human Body as the Object of Intention}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Intentionality and the governing of one\uc1\u8217\'92s own body without intermediation. The objectification of others\uc1\u8217\'92 bodies and the \uc1\u8220\'93emptying\uc1\u8221\'94 of their subjectivity.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab IV.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Memory and the Human Landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97The lack of correspondence between the human landscape perceived in the present and the human landscape deriving from the period of formation of the one perceiving. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab V.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The Distance Imposed by the Human Landscape}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97The distance between the perceived human landscape and the represented human landscape arises not only from the difference in times but also from }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}ways of being-in-the-world}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0} that depend on the emotions and the presence of one\uc1\u8217\'92s own body.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VI.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Education}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Recommends that an integral education embody coherent thinking as contact with one\uc1\u8217\'92s own registers of thinking; that it should consider awareness and emotional development as contact with oneself and others; and that it should not overlook practices that bring into play the full range of each person\uc1\u8217\'92s corporal resources. Distinguishes between education as formation, information as the integration of data through study, and practice as a form of study.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}History}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Until now history has been looked at from the \uc1\u8220\'93outside,\uc1\u8221\'94 without taking human intentionality into account.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab VIII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Ideologies}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97In times when ideologies are in crisis there arise \uc1\u8220\'93ideologemas\uc1\u8221\'94 that claim to represent reality itself. Such is the case with so-called \uc1\u8220\'93pragmatism.\uc1\u8221\'94}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab IX.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Violence}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Nonviolence as a methodology of social and political struggle does not require justification. It is a system in which violence predominates that needs justification in order to impose itself. Distinguishes between pacifism and nonviolence. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab X.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Law}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Considers both the origin of law and the theme of power as a precondition for any law. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XI.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}The State}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97The State as an apparatus of intermediation between the real power held by a part of society and the social whole.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Religion}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Religions as \uc1\u8220\'93externality\uc1\u8221\'94 inasmuch as they attempt to speak about God and not about the inner register of God in the human being.}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi-936\li229\ri-431\s37\sl240\slmult1\itap0\tqdec\tx0\tx180{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \tab XIII.\tab }{\s37\f0\fs22\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Open Roads}{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\uc1\u8212\'97Concludes by inviting the reader to study and further develop important themes of the human landscape that have not been addressed in this work. }{\s37\f0\fs22\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
